is not reassigned in the loop - `s` is. `h := s.handler` creates a new variable 
each iteration in modern Go (Go 1.22+), but `ctx` and `event` are from the funct
ion parameters, so they\'re stable for the entire `Publish` call. Actually in Go
1.22, loop variables are per-iteration, so `s`, `h` are per-iteration. But `even
t` is the parameter, stable. `ctx` is the parameter, stable. So actually the clo
sure `func() { h(ctx, event) }` captures `h`, `ctx`, `event`. With Go 1.22 seman
tics, `h` is per-iteration. So this is safe IF the go version is 1.22+.\n\nLet m
e check go.mod to see the Go version.',
